    <bioghist>Born in South Bend, Indiana, Boger was the owner of Tryon Repair Service in Charlotte, North Carolina. He attended Camp Roosevelt, an ROTC summer camp sponsored by Chicago Public Schools at Mona Lake, near Muskegon, Michigan in 1920. Boger was married to Nell Mosteller Boger and died in 1956 at the age of 54.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Photocopy of Churchill Boger's diary from Camp Roosevelt dated July 1-August 28, 1920; photocopy of Boger's death certificate from 1956.</scopecontent>
